      <div class="mission-text">
        <p>1- <strong>Sponsor</strong> under privileged children currently educated in local Hong Kong Schools. To provide:<br>
        <i class="fa fa-circle" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 10px;"></i> School uniforms <br>
        <i class="fa fa-circle" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 10px;"></i> Official text books (not supplied free by the Education Board) <br>
        <i class="fa fa-circle" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 10px;"></i> Stationary <br>
        <i class="fa fa-circle" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 10px;"></i> Pens and other equipment <br>
        2- Liaise with the <strong>school authorities</strong> (head teacher) to respond to the future needs of pupils and the
        school. <br>
        3- <strong>Provide school books</strong> and general reading books to build up the school library to encourage all
        pupils to discover the pleasure of reading. <br>
        4- Ensure that the pupils receive a balanced and healthy daily meal. For those families that are
        unable to do this, provide a free lunch meal for the pupils within the school’s catering facilities. <br>
        5- Providing equipment, <strong>like computers</strong>, to supplement those supplied by the school authorities. <br>
        6- <strong>Schools</strong> that are currently being helped are: <br>
        <i class="fa fa-circle" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 10px;"></i> St Claire’s Girls School, 50 Mt Davis Road, Pok Fu Lam <br>
        <i class="fa fa-circle" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 10px;"></i> St Stephen’s Church College, 62 Pok Fu Lam Road, Pok Fu Lam <br>
        <i class="fa fa-circle" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 10px;"></i> The main goal of MAYAA is not to grow too fast! <br> <br>
        We strive to <strong>consolidate</strong> the work which is currently already done: <br>
        <i class="fa fa-circle" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 10px;"></i> <strong>Improve</strong> our capacity to sponsor a child up to his school graduation + help him to get a post
        graduate certificate or Professional training. <br>
        <i class="fa fa-circle" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 10px;"></i> Based on actions already undertaken elsewhere, <strong>develop similar educational support</strong> to
        underprivileged children in Hong Kong. <br>
        <i class="fa fa-circle" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 10px;"></i> <strong>Help to improve local school facilities</strong> where these may be lacking, such as extra library
        books, additional computers … <br>
        <i class="fa fa-circle" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 10px;"></i> Ensure that children receive at least <strong>one balanced meal</strong> per day. Either by providing the
        meal or sponsoring within the school catering structure. <br>
        <i class="fa fa-circle" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 10px;"></i> To identify children and families in need by working closely with the school authorities, and
        school teachers. <br>
        <i class="fa fa-circle" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size: 10px;"></i> Identify children in <strong>need educationally</strong> and provide extracurricular teaching to give them
        that extra help to keep up.
        </p>
